snippet.textDisplay: Tive que pesquisar aqui, encontrei: "mRNA vaccines have strands of genetic material called mRNA inside a special coating. That coating protects the mRNA from enzymes in the body that would otherwise break it down. It also helps the mRNA enter the dendritic cells and macrophages in the lymph node near the vaccination site.". Isto é , a cobertura ao redor do mRNA é o que permite a entrada
